How are ratings calculated?

Amazon Customer
4.0 out of 5 stars Great quality, but one key detail wrong
Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2020
Color: RavenclawVerified Purchase
Great quality tie. Supposedly made from the same material as the non-woven version, but feels much different to me. Color accuracy is better than the non-woven version, with the stripes looking more silver in this version than the white-ish color in the regular non-woven one. Ravenclaw crest is beautifully woven in and as a result there is a color difference that the non-woven version, but I like the appearance better with this one.

The one major issue I have with this version is that it doesn't replicate the movie ties in one key detail, stripe direction. Being set in the UK, the ties of the Hogwarts student all have Euro-style Rep striping, meaning the stripes go from the wearer's left shoulder down to the wearer's right waist. The non-woven version gets this detail correct. This version however uses the American style Rep stripe, which goes in the opposite direction. Not a big deal if you are not hung up on such details but for detail oriented people this could be a deal breaker.

Overall this is a very good quality tie. I could see myself wearing it for work if it were not for the Crest at the bottom. Although I could wear it underneath a vest or sweater.
